Time-resolved EFISHG results of both 3D and 2D/3D hybrid PSCs. (a) shows the 3D and 2D/3D hybrid samples; the dotted lines' difference presents the charge accumulation in the 3D sample. (b,c) illustrates the time-resolved EFISHG measurements of the fresh and aged 3D and 2D/3D hybrid samples. AC square wave (− 3 V) with a pulse width of 100 µs was applied to the Au electrode with reference to FTO.

